  "prompt": "What are the top rated Hollywood movies in 2017?",
  "response": "Here are some of the top-rated Hollywood movies from 2017, based on critical acclaim and audience reception:\n\n1. **Get Out** - Directed by Jordan Peele, this social thriller/horror film received widespread praise for its screenplay, direction, and commentary on race relations.\n\n2. **Lady Bird** - Greta Gerwig's coming-of-age film captured hearts with its heartfelt storytelling and strong performances, particularly from Saoirse Ronan.\n\n3. **Dunkirk** - Christopher Nolan's war epic was lauded for its immersive storytelling, visual cinematography, and unique narrative structure.\n\n4. **Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri** - This dark comedy-drama, directed by Martin McDonagh, earned acclaim for its writing and performances, especially from Frances McDormand.\n\n5. **The Shape of Water** - Guillermo del Toro's fantasy romance won multiple awards, including the Academy Award for Best Picture. Its unique storytelling and visual style were highly praised.\n\n6. **Call Me by Your Name** - A romantic drama directed by Luca Guadagnino, celebrated for its beautiful cinematography, writing, and performances, especially by Timoth\u00e9e Chalamet.\n\n7. **Blade Runner 2049** - The sequel to the original Blade Runner film, directed by Denis Villeneuve, was noted for its stunning visuals and profound storytelling.\n\n8. **Coco** - This animated film from Pixar was celebrated for its animation, music, and emotional depth, focusing on family and cultural heritage.\n\n9. **Wonder Woman** - Directed by Patty Jenkins, this superhero film received acclaim for its strong lead performance by Gal Gadot and its fresh take on the genre.\n\n10. **The Big Sick** - A romantic comedy based on the real-life courtship of Kumail Nanjiani and Emily V. Gordon, it was praised for its heartfelt storytelling and humor.\n\nThese films received a mix of critical acclaim, audience favorites, and various awards recognition throughout the year.",
